long_desc.thetext:
-I${MPI_FORTRAN_MOD_DIR} does not work on RHEL6/RHEL7 (see bug #1409235)

Fedora and RHEL use different value for MPI_FORTRAN_MOD_DIR in the modulefiles under /etc/modulefiles/mpi*, but the fortran mod files are installed under %{_fmoddir}/%{name} on both Fedora/RHEL

Fedora:

MPI_FORTRAN_MOD_DIR	%{_fmoddir}/%{name}

RHEL:

MPI_FORTRAN_MOD_DIR	%{_fmoddir}/%{name}-%{_arch}

This means on EPEL one cannot use MPI_FORTRAN_MOD_DIR directly and instead

-I%{_fmoddir}/%{name}
